A.  OVERVIEW

The Austrian computer software market is characterized by approximately 300
suppliers, most of which are small enterprises. The 40 largest software firms
are almost exclusively companies which have operated at least 10 years in the
EDP sector. On the average, it requires about 5 to 6 years for firms to
achieve an annual turnover of approximately AS 10 million (USD 860,000). The
sectors with the fastest growth rate are in the sectors of manufacturing,
logistics, trade and application software.

Given their comparatively small size, Austrian software firms are satisfied
with low turnover -- especially those with clients with over 500 employees and
sales ranging from AS 1 million and AS 1.2 million (USD 90,000 - USD 100,000)
to a maximum of AS 4 million (USD 340,000). In Austria, there are only about
350 large enterprises with over 500 employees. These firms transact business
with about 40 percent of the software suppliers, which demonstrates the
importance of large enterprises for the development of a competitive domestic
software industry. Target enterprises with 50 to 500 employees are more
important customers for independent Austrian software firms than for
international suppliers.

Sixty percent of Austrian domestic software production is tied to a specific
operating system; 35 percent to a specific computer category; and 25 percent
to a specific hardware producer. About 80 percent of the Austrian software
producers cooperate with hardware manufacturers (mostly foreign firms), while
50 percent work with software houses and 30 percent with universities. The
cooperation is primarily concentrated in the areas of distribution, consulting
training and development.

The total Austrian market is estimated at AS 5 billion (USD 430 million) for
1993. The growth rate in 1993 vis-a-vis 1992 was 8 percent. The estimated
growth rate for 1994 is 10 percent. The U.S. market share was approximately 15
percent in 1993.

In Austria, no accurate measurement methods have been developed for sales,
import, export and production figures for application software. Figures in
this report are based on various market, industry, press, and association
sources and amount to "informed estimates," which varied from source to
source. A point on which all industy analysts agreed, however, was the
prediction that software will become the driving force of the Austrian
computer industry.


