C.  MARKET ASSESSMENT

There are great expectations in the fields of office automation and
manufacturing, which about 50 percent of software enterprises plan to
penetrate. The main focus in the commercial field is on
management-information systems.

Software firms with a significant turnover are mostly engaged in business
with banks, insurance companies and other financial service institutions.
These target groups have the highest market growth potential over the next
few years. Also important for these suppliers is the public sector and, to a
lesser extent, the health sector. The public sector and most of the health
sector are already covered by foreign suppliers.

Subsectors which have the highest potential for software suppliers are:
industry; financial services; public administration; trade; health; energy;
production and distribution; and data transmission.

Media advertising is particularly important for application software. There
are several computer magazines available in Austria, that are well suited for
software promotion and publicity. There is one exhibition in Austria which is
recommended for effective software promotion.

In addition, the advantages of locally held, well-publicized software
seminars are not being overlooked by major manufacturers of hardware such as
IBM, SIEMENS-NIXDORF and Digital Equipment Corporation. Seminars have many
benefits to offer suppliers of software packages. They are relatively
inexpensive to stage, provide an opportunity to meet existing and potential
users, and can focus on hardware or software, or a combination of both.
Instructions can be mixed with a judicious blend of salesmanship, and dialog
is usually the result. This provides the much needed feedback of user opinion
and requirements for the manufacturer or software writer.  Software seminars
and symposia in Austria will become a growing service industry in the next
decade.

Large company demand is mostly directed toward worldwide horizontal, best
selling packages. Small users concentrate on management programs, both
standard and customized. The German market has a strong influence on the
Austrian software market. The legislation of the two countries allows
administration packages developed in Germany similar viability in the
Austrian market place.


D.  BEST SALES PROSPECTS

The best opportunities for sales of U.S. manufactured application software
products in Austria appear to be in systems engineering and applications
consultancy, data bank and communications software/office automation,
education, export administration, CASE, CIM and quality control.

