E.  COMPETITIVE SITUATION

IBM is the largest software and services vendor in Austria. DEC and
Siemens-Nixdorf(SNI) generate revenues of less than half those of the market
leader and have not shown significant growth over the past two years. In
fact, SNI probably suffered some loss of client base to competitors during
the uncertain period at the time of its take-over.

Management Data is a twenty year old company operating in Austria (Vienna,
Innsbruck, and Salzburg), Germany, Hungary, the UK and Singapore. It has a
network of agents across Europe, and in Japan and South Africa. Its main
specialization is international banking software, primarily selling turnkey
systems.

Dataservice is wholly-owned subsidiary of the Austrian bank "CREDITANSTALT".
It has a strong PC orientation, as well as a wide range of processing
services. The firm specializes in banking, insurance and manufacturing
systems. Beko has an engineering bias across a wide range of sectors and
specialized in manufacturing, laboratory and general business administration
systems.

